  Source:
    Title: Manava-dharma-sastra
    Locus: II 88
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=Closing the Doors of the Senses
Commentary: |
  This recalls Plato's doctrine of the charioteer and steeds in Phaedrus.
---
Let a wise man, like a driver of horses, exert diligence in restraint of his
senses straying among seductive sendual objects.
